    {
        "content": "<p>My first attempt was to maximally apply the lemma:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">iAdd_union_eq_add_iAdd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ι</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ι₁</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⊕</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ι₂</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">s₁</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Function</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Embedding</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">inl</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">s₂</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Function</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Embedding</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">inr</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but I didn't learn anything from that, so I tried</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">convert</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">iAdd_union_eq_add_iAdd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ι</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ι₁</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⊕</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ι₂</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">s₁</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Function</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Embedding</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">inl</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">s₂</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Function</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Embedding</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">inr</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but that worked, so it seemed likely that <code>convert</code> was dealing with some instances that didn't match</p>",
        "id": 469113730,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1725979248
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And then I noticed the <code>open Classical</code> I should have flagged immediately, because I know it's dangerous</p>",
        "id": 469114034,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1725979287
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Im particular, the reason it doesn't work is because one of the decidability instances on <code>ι₁ ⊕ ι₂</code> is <code>Classical.propDecidable</code>, while the other is obtained by combining two decidability instances on <code>ι₁</code> and <code>ι₂</code>  (themselves <code>Classical.propDecidable</code>) via <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Sum.instDecidableEq_batteries#doc\">docs#Sum.instDecidableEq_batteries</a></p>",
        "id": 469114840,
        "sender_full_name": "Mauricio Collares",
        "timestamp": 1725979392
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you add an <code>using 3</code> to the end of Ruben's <code>convert</code> call and do <code>set_option pp.all true</code>, then you'll see the diamond</p>",
        "id": 469116734,
        "sender_full_name": "Mauricio Collares",
        "timestamp": 1725979630
    },
    {
